Sign in Report this job Hello and welcome to start your next journey with Sellforte! üëã We are on a mission to help retailers and consumer brands accelerate their growth by making smarter data-driven marketing decisions. Sellforte is a Marketing Mix Modelling (MMM) SaaS for marketing teams and agencies to holistically evaluate and improve the effectiveness of marketing and promotional activities. We do not only show cool marketing metrics or fancy dashboards ‚Äì we deliver real impact based on Bayesian methods and data science. There also are current bigger developments in the marketing industry, where new privacy norms are eradicating measurement by user-level attribution, and probabilistic and econometric solutions like Sellforte are expected to gain ground. You will join a team of fifteen bad-ass data scientists, who are the spine for our business, and you‚Äôll work closely with many experts from various fields (for example Customer Success Managers, Software Developers, Sales). In addition, you'll get the chance to work with smaller and bigger marketers and consumer brands and make a real impact in their marketing by offering insights based on the data and modelling. üéØ What you will do‚ÄØas a Customer Data Scientist: As a Customer Data Scientist, your ultimate goal is to support our enterprise customers, i.e. to ensure Sellforte service is running smoothly and that they get value from the service. To achieve these goals, you are working in a Customer Delivery team with Customer Success Managers and other Data Scientists. Specifically, you will Do exploratory data analysis with customer data (using e.g. Python and pandas), solve customer-specific issues and business problems. Help onboard new customers to our marketing analytics service/platform: set up data flow from customer to Sellforte, configure the modelling, and communicate technical solutions to customers. Meet customers, e.g. in weekly/monthly meetings. Participate in product development: communicate new learnings and insights, as well as develop new features and automation directly to the product. Collaborate with other data scientists and data engineers to implement and train predictive machine learning models, such as time series forecasting Bayesian models to statistically infer causal impacts. What we hope from you: üå§ Previous experience working as a data scientist, analytics consultant, or a similar role in the industry, having applied data analysis or ML/AI to real business problems. Good communication skills in English. This is a customer facing role and it is crucial to be able to explain deeply technical issues to non-technical people. Ability to identify and solve business problems based on data and quick analysis.‚ÄØPositive and get-things-done attitude in general. Hands-on technical skills especially with Python. We hope that you would already be located in the Helsinki/Espoo region in Finland, or you would be willing to relocate there. Relocation support to Finland is possible. For GDPR and contractual reasons, the job needs to be done within Europe. üéØ What Sellforte offers to you: Work in an open and easy-going startup/scaleup environment with nice colleagues üöÄ International and multi-cultural team. We have 13+ different nationalities working in 5 different countries! Globally unique product which is developed with modern technologies (such as Python, AWS, Airflow, Stan etc) A low hierarchy and enjoyable ride. We try to find that extra spark of fun that makes the journey worthwhile to ourselves and to the people around us. Sellforteans are bunch of warm hearted and kind people who enjoy delivering impact and growing the business together! Growth ‚Äì both business and individual. We try to build product and data science culture within the company, including regular data science or data engineering talks and presentations. üçï Flexibility to find your work-life balance - We understand that nine to five doesn't fit for all. We have also flexible remote culture and f2f working possibilities. As a company, we are trying to support different type of working, whether it is online or office. This means that teams and team members can choose what is the best way of working for them. As an example, we have fully remote employees and those, who like to work from the office on daily basis. Of course, your opinion matters! Benefits, such as healthcare,‚ÄØlunch and activity benefits, full holidays‚ÄØfrom the start of your employment‚ÄØ(5 weeks/year), phone and other working equipment,‚ÄØoption program, and home care services in case of sick children. How to apply: Do you feel that this position matches what you are looking for? Let‚Äôs start this‚ÄØincredible journey together by getting to‚ÄØknow each other! The‚ÄØrecruitment process consists of intro call with our Co-founder & Chief Science Officer, and one or two interview sessions, including both a more traditional interview discussion and a data science case exercise. We try to include members from your future teams in the interview process for the best outcome. During the process you‚Äôll meet a lot of Sellforteans and get to see the product we‚Äôre working with. We hope to hear from you soon! üòä Show more Show less Seniority level Entry level Employment type Full-time Job function Engineering and Information Technology Industries Software Development Referrals increase your chances of interviewing at Sellforte by 2x See who you know

Sign in Report this job We are looking for an expert in artificial intelligence and data analytics. As a Data Scientist you will work closely with our customers nationally as well as participate internationally funded projects. CSC is a non-profit limited liability company with a special mission, owned by the Finnish Government and higher education institutions. We offer and develop high-level ICT services for research, education, culture, public administration and companies so that they can succeed and benefit society as a whole. The position is located in the business area that provides solutions for education and research administration. The Data Scientist's job description includes participating in the planning, conceptualisation and implementation of artificial intelligence and data analytics solutions that meet our customers' needs. Additionally, you get to apply your expertise with supporting our business operations and service development, and spar with CSC's experts in finding the best practices. One example of an international project is the OpenWebSearch.eu project, which aims to develop a European open web index (OWI) with the cooperation of an international network of researchers and experts. The project lays the foundation for an open and extensible European Open Web Search and Analysis Infrastructure (OWSAI) based on European values, legislation and standards. The Data Scientist will be a part of CSC's expert team, but is responsible for conducting development work independently. We are seeking for a Data Scientist who has competence and practical experience in versatile analytics and artificial intelligence methods, work methods and data processing. In addition we hope that you have Verified knowledge of machine learning and data science, especially language models, NLP Work experience with artificial intelligence solutions and methods Pro-active and initiative mindset Ability to further refine customers' preliminary ideas and needs, and produce understandable proposals, concepts and solutions Ability to cooperate and good communication skills Experience in project work and working with customers Motivation and desire to share learnings, and to support colleagues in the implementation of artificial intelligence and analytics solutions Knowledge of English and Finnish (basic level) language skills Previous experience in high-performance computing (HPC) is considered as strength. As tools we use e.g. the following: Python, R and Java. In addition to your closest colleagues, you have almost 700 experts from the entire organization to support your work. We offer you interesting work in a supportive atmosphere with the opportunity to develop your own expertise in an international company with long traditions. At CSC, your colleagues are friendly, enthusiastic and curious top-notch experts in their field. The extensive personnel benefits offered by CSC include, for example, flexible remote work and vacation arrangements, comprehensive occupational health care services, incentive bonus system, subsidized sports, recreation and cultural opportunities, lunch benefits and modern work spaces in Keilaniemi, Espoo. Please submit your application through our recruitment website https://csc.fi/en/careers/ by 2.8.2024 . We encourage you to apply as soon as possible, as interviews can be held during the application period. The position will be filled when a suitable person is found. Sign in Report this job Are you a data professional and familiar with Databricks? We are strengthening our Databricks competences and want you to join our cozy and caring Connected Data unit with 400 data professionals. What is Databricks? Based on Apache Spark, Databricks is used to process large workloads of data that allows collaboration between data scientists, data engineers, and business analysts to derive actionable insights with one-click setup, streamlined workflows, and an interactive workspace. Today, Databricks has functionalities ranging from unified cloud-based data platform to the latest in generative AI. In Solita, we believe in the power of data, and we work hard to make high-quality data available for all purposes. Data is no longer just a property of operational systems or reporting, but we are seeing the convergence of different systems and viewpoints to data. Promoting the use of modern DevOps and MLOps methods, we believe that data platforms need to be built using the best practices from the software industry. We view Databricks as a solid technology to build the dream data platform together with our customers and to create impact that lasts. We will provide you access to versatile projects that interest you. You can take advantage of your own strengths, learn new things, and develop into an even stronger data expert. Our customers come from a variety of industries, both private and public. We will do our best to provide you with projects from industries that interest you most. About You A suitable background could be e.g. Data Engineer, Data Scientist, Machine Learning Engineer or even Mathematician. Or maybe you are DevOps or MLOps professional, Full Stack or Back-End Developer with experience in data integration or databases. You already have experience in using Databricks and want to become even better in it. You want to scale up your thinking and knowledge to serve even wider set of data use cases. Strong people skills and the courage to challenge customers are essential as a consultant. Our values caring, easy-going, courage, and passion guides everything we do, and we hope these resonates with you as well. You can work remotely (in Finland) or in our offices all over Finland. The readiness for occasional travel is an advantage, as we have customers and operations in addition to Finland (e.g. in Sweden and Germany). However, traveling is not an absolute requirement. Solita as an employer Solita is an international Nordic consulting company with Finnish roots. Our Connected Data unit employs data engineering, data science, data visualisation, business performance management and master data management specialists, as well as a group of data architects and data integration experts. We help customers to solve problems and aim to create sustainable solutions ‚Äì the kind we ourselves would be proud to use and maintain. Let‚Äôs talk? Let‚Äôs find out whether we could provide you next career challenge! Share your cv or LinkedIn profile by 7th of August. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. Establish and implement best practices and standards for data governance across the lifecycle data domain. Develop the end-to-end lifecycle data operational process, ensuring timely, quality and accurate data collection, processing, storage, and distribution to various stakeholders and systems. Drive the adoption and utilization of data analytics and data science tools and methods to generate insights and recommendations that enhance the customer experience and business outcomes throughout the lifecycle. Establish and develop a high-performing team of lifecycle data professionals, providing them with coaching, mentoring, and development opportunities. Foster a culture of collaboration, innovation, and continuous improvement within the lifecycle data CoE team, reaching across the organization. Accountable for development and optimization of data architecture that supports the lifecycle data domain, ensuring scalability, reliability, and performance from a business perspective. To be successful in this role, you should have: Extensive experience in leading and managing data teams, projects, and programs, preferably in a large and complex organization. Strong understanding of data architecture, data integration and data governance to drive change across the organization. Solid experience in leading and applying data management, data engineering, data analysis, or data science within lifecycle data domain or similar. Proven track record of delivering successful data projects and programs that drive business performance and customer satisfaction. Strong strategic thinking, problem-solving, and decision-making skills, with the ability to align data initiatives and solutions with business goals and customer needs. High level of initiative, creativity, and innovation, with the ability to identify and pursue new opportunities and solutions for data-driven value creation and improvement. Strong collaborative and influencing skills, with the ability to translate complex concepts and findings into simple and actionable insights and recommendations. Why you & us? We at W√§rtsil√§ believe in empowerment, ownership and taking responsibility of our work. We support each other‚Äôs growth and co-creation is the true basis of our innovation. This is a rare, operational and actionable data-driven experience that requires a good mix of technical and stakeholder engagement skills. Expertise in statistical analysis, including hypothesis testing, experimentation using statistical software packages in Python, R, or equivalent for product development (preferably consumer-facing). Our apps (iOS and Android) have the industry‚Äôs highest ratings, largely thanks to our customer-first-mindset, which shows in how we build products and run operations. In June 2022 we officially joined forces with DoorDash. Combined, we have a presence in 27 countries, 23 of which operate with the Wolt brand and app. Wolt and DoorDash continue largely independently, with Wolt‚Äôs name, brand, product, technology and team. Working in Product Development at Wolt At Wolt, we‚Äôre about getting things done. You‚Äôll probably enjoy it here if you like taking ownership, developing yourself and being around friendly, humble and ambitious people. The behind the scenes of Wolt is run by an awesome bunch of over 400+ planners, builders, designers and data crunchers. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. Sign in Report this job Are you ready to shape the future of data strategy and architecture in a dynamic and innovative environment? We are seeking a visionary Chief Data Architect to lead our data initiatives and drive the evolution of our data landscape. As a Chief Data Architect, your role will be pivotal in shaping the data strategy across our organization. This involves creating a comprehensive strategy that aligns with our current business objectives and encompasses both our SaaS business and Enterprise aspects of our data landscape. Establishing and enforcing data governance policies to ensure data accuracy, security, and regulatory compliance will be a part of your responsibilities. In this role, you‚Äôll be working closely with various stakeholders within the organization to understand their data needs and translate them into data strategies and solutions. Designing and optimizing data models to support robust data architecture, ensuring efficient data storage, retrieval, and analysis, while also making data readily accessible and usable for machine learning applications, will be essential. Continual optimization of the data infrastructure for improved performance, scalability, and reliability, as well as ensuring compatibility with machine learning workflows, will be a key part of your responsibilities. In addition, you will be instrumental in envisioning the future of our data infrastructure, taking into account the evolving needs of our organization and the role of various components. Staying abreast of industry trends and emerging technologies to keep our data architecture at the cutting edge will be expected. Products and Cloud Engineering & Operations business function is responsible for ensuring that Basware continues to provide its customers with industry leading SaaS solutions to deliver true automation for the CFO‚Äôs office. As a global team, they create and execute the product strategy, new product innovations, roadmap, design, product development, and product launches for Basware‚Äôs global product portfolio. Together with other Baswareans, Products and Cloud Engineering & Operation ensures that our customers can successfully meet their business objectives through cooperating with Basware and using our product and service portfolio. To succeed in this role, you need the following skills and qualifications: Experience in mapping out architecture-level solutions for both business decision-makers and the implementing experts in an understandable way. Experience of data modeling, data warehousing, streaming, databases (SQL/NoSQL), ETL/ELT, semantic indexes, etc. and big data technologies like Spark. Understanding of data security measures, encryption standards, and best practices to ensure the integrity and security of the data. Hands-on experience in solution development, including the ability to handle data fluidly (parse, transfer, store, edit) and build data pipelines in suitable languages, such as Python or SQL. You are willing to work on hands-on projects and take a proactive role in the development process and have previous experience or familiarity with standard software development practices and tools. Familiar with the concepts of DevOps and Infrastructure-as-Code Knowledge of data visualization tools like Tableau, PowerBI, or similar are a plus. While not a must, having a basic understanding of machine learning algorithms can be beneficial, especially when working closely with data scientists or ML teams. Knowledge and experience of the Data Mesh framework is a plus. Next steps We would love to hear from you! Go to careers.basware.com and click "I'm interested". Our recruitment process will include pre-employment actions such as reference checks. Our offering We offer flexibility in how you work, giving you the freedom and support to deliver your best results. With over $1 billion invested annually in R&D, at Thermo Fisher Scientific you‚Äôll help tackle some of the world‚Äôs toughest challenges, from giving cancer patients hope, ensuring safe drinking water and helping law enforcement tackle cases through forensics. We empower our teams to put science into meaningful action and give our R&D colleagues the autonomy, resources and tools they need to take science a step beyond. This position is based in Vantaa, and we are working closely with our other Immunodiagnostics division colleagues in Uppsala, where Thermo Fisher develops, manufactures, and markets complete blood test systems to support the clinical diagnosis and monitoring of allergy, asthma, and autoimmune diseases. We are the global leader in in-vitro allergy testing and the European leader in autoimmunity diagnostics. Our Finland locations include Vantaa and Joensuu, employing over 800 professionals supporting functions such as production, instrument and reagent manufacturing, R&D, marketing, sales, quality, administrative support, and supply chain. We hire experts in different fields including engineering, chemistry, microbiology, and bioinformatics. Our Vantaa site develops pipettes and microplate instruments as well as clinical chemistry and industrial chemistry analysers, laboratory automation solutions and food safety kits. It is conveniently located close to the Vantaankoski railway station. Discover Impactful Work Are you looking for a meaningful job in an international company with strong values? Would you like to use your knowledge as a senior data scientist and have a possibility to help our customers in how they conduct their diagnoses around the world? If you‚Äôre passionate about providing high quality products, we encourage you to apply. We are strengthening our data science team, and you will play a meaningful role in providing data analysis and simulations relevant to our organization and development of our diagnostic devices. We offer you an exciting and rewarding career where you will get an excellent opportunity to develop your technical and professional skills in one of the world's largest life science companies. How will you make an impact? As a (Senior) Data Scientist, you bring wealth of analytical thinking to our Vantaa Team to help us in providing healthcare professionals with advanced diagnostic technologies. You will, for example: Participate in defining right data sources, collecting, and analysing large amount of data. Collaborate with software engineers, product and project management, and verification teams by communicating your data analysis results. Contribute to building coherent data strategy. Participate in different kind of investigations relevant to our customer support. Communicate your results for both technical and non-technical audience. Keys to Success To succeed in this role, you are agile, resilient, and take ownership for your own development. You never compromise on quality and always act responsibly remembering that our customers always come first. You speak and write excellent English. We operate in a heavily regulated industry, so it is important to have a structured way of working and document your work in line with the quality system. You find it easy to collaborate and connect with others, and you are comfortable in leading and motivating your team members. How Will You Get There Bachelor‚Äôs or Master‚Äôs degree from suitable area (e.g., engineering, computer science, information technology). Proven experience as Data Scientist or Data Analyst, including analytical and statistical expertise, and programming skills. Hands-on experience with data science tools (analysis, visualization, etc.) You are analytical and love to solve challenges with data. You are clear in communicating your intensions, collaborating with your peers, and proficient in English language. Benefits We offer employment with an innovative, forward-thinking organization, and outstanding career and development prospects. We offer an exciting company culture that stands for integrity, intensity, involvement, and innovation! Examples of benefits Compensation on various methods from annual bonus scheme to colleague recognition program. Variety of occupational health care services. Epassi leisure benefit and gym on Vantaa site Various hobby clubs with company sponsorship such as golf club, boating club, sport club etc. Possibility to take part in our charity work. Career development and progression possibilities offered by our global network. Our comprehensive training platform and programs. Sign in Report this job Wanted: We are looking for an experienced Data Engineer ready and excited to take on the challenge of making Upright's Net Impact Platform the #1 impact data platform globally. The Upright Platform is currently used by 200+ institutional investment organizations and corporations, mainly in Europe and North America. We are now looking for a senior professional who can help us take our data integrations to the next level to enable global scaling. Upright‚Äôs Net Impact Platform uses data from various sources to calculate the impact of business activities on the world, so this information is at the core of everything we do. Your job will be to take the lead on designing, developing and orchestrating our data pipelines. You will work together with our data scientists and software engineers to design systems that ingest, integrate and serve information that Upright‚Äôs customers use to optimize their impact. You will also work on deploying, maintaining and monitoring these data pipelines, including the underlying infrastructure. We mainly work with unstructured and semi-structured text as well as tabular data from a large variety of public and proprietary data sources. Depending on your interest and skills, you might additionally take an important role in cultivating high-performing data practices and culture at Upright or researching and validating sources of external data that should be integrated into Upright‚Äôs platform. You could also be working together with data scientists to productize data and to train and deploy machine learning models as well as publish and present Upright‚Äôs approaches to integrating data from different sources. The exact role will be tailored to fit the background, experience, skill level and interests of the chosen person. SIGNS FOR BEING A GREAT MATCH WITH THIS ROLE INCLUDE: Solid track record of internal passion for excellence: you have gotten things done clearly better than what was required/expected from you, as you enjoy doing things well Sense of urgency and drive to get the job done with tight deadlines Good handle on SQL and Python. Scala and other tools for data intensive programming are considered a plus Experience in writing production-grade ETL pipelines, ideally on distributed systems Experience in data pipeline orchestration systems such as Apache Airflow Experience in cloud services such as AWS, GCP or Azure Experience MLOps, and data and ML model versioning more broadly Experience in DevOps, infrastructure as code and containers Ability to work both autonomously and as part of a team Ability to see the big picture and prioritize work accordingly Ability to communicate clearly both verbally and in writing ADDITIONALLY, WE VALUE THE FOLLOWING QUALIFICATIONS: Understanding of optimization techniques like denormalization, caching and compression, and when to use them Experience working with company disclosures and financial data Track record in writing production quality software, e.g., in Scala or Typescript Familiarity with Upright‚Äôs platform tech stack (Node, TypeScript, PostgreSQL and React) WHAT WE OFFER: A chance to join a quickly growing and highly ambitious impact SaaS company with a mission that matters A fun and kind team with exceptional people who care about what they do Exciting professional growth opportunities Competitive compensation, including stock options and a comprehensive healthcare package MISSION THAT MATTERS Upright is on a mission to incentivize companies to optimize their net impact by enabling science-based decision-making for investors, customers, employees, and public sector agents. To do that, Upright develops a proprietary data model based on an open-access database of 200M+ scientific articles and artificial intelligence to quantify the net impact of companies on people, planet, society, and knowledge creation. In addition to net impact, Upright produces data on UN SDG alignment, EU taxonomy, and EU SFDR PAI indicators. Currently, our impact data platform is used by 200+ institutional investors and companies, such as Nasdaq, Nordea, EQT and Nokia. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. As the international side of Doordash business, Wolt is active in 27 countries outside of the US and growing. As a Data Scientist at Wolt, you‚Äôll dive deep into our data to tackle crucial business challenges. You will diagnose problem areas, develop new metrics, design experiments, uncover foundational causal relationships in our data, and influence strategic decisions. This role combines scientific expertise with stakeholder engagement, positioning you at the forefront of driving business outcomes. We‚Äôre seeking someone who enjoys finding patterns amidst chaos, is excited to build solutions from the ground up, and has a proven track record in using data science to solve business problems. You will work closely with Product, Engineering, Design, and Operations teams to guide measurement strategies and tactical decisions, helping to expand the Wolt platform globally. If you take ownership of business outcomes and are proactive in driving change, we want you on our team! Our offering to you The online delivery platform that Wolt is building will offer you interesting and complex challenges together with the opportunities to create a big impact with your skills. Lots of geolocational and temporal data in real-time combined with differences in the economics and dynamics of the cities we operate in make Wolt both a challenging and so interesting company to practice analytics. You can choose the location from our tech hubs in Berlin, Helsinki and Stockholm, or you can work entirely remotely anywhere in Germany, Finland and Sweden. Read more about how we work. Our humble expectations Degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, or a related field. Have over 5 years of experience in a data science or analytics position within an industry or research setting. Expertise in statistical analysis, including hypothesis testing, experimentation, and regression analysis using statistical software packages in Python, Matlab, R, or equivalent. Expertise in causal inference and quasi-experimentation. Proficiency in writing structured and efficient SQL queries for large data sets. Relentless pursuit of new ideas and data sources, and the ability to systematically tackle ambiguous problems with a data-driven, hypothesis-based approach. Be analytical, inquisitive, and a self-starter who is motivated to achieve results and collaborate with colleagues both inside and outside of the team. Next Steps The position will be filled as soon as we find the right person, so make sure to apply as soon as you realize you really, really want to join us! Combined, we have a presence in 27 countries, 23 of which operate with the Wolt brand and app. Wolt and DoorDash continue largely independently, with Wolt‚Äôs name, brand, product, technology and team. Working in Product Development at Wolt At Wolt, we‚Äôre about getting things done. The Data Modeler will work collaboratively with the data architect, data engineers, data analysts / BI specialists, DBA, IT and business units to help address the business‚Äô data and analytical needs. The data modeler will design, implement, and document data architecture and data modelling solutions, which include the use of relational, dimensional, and NoSQL databases. These solutions will support enterprise information management, business intelligence, machine learning, data science, and other business interests. THE DAY-TO-DAY Implement business and IT data requirements through new data strategies and designs across all data models (relational, dimensional, and NoSQL) and data tools (reporting, visualization, analytics, and machine learning) Work with business and application/solution teams to define data flows, design logic for data cleansing, and develop data models Modelling of data to meet the development and ongoing requirements of the various layers (cleansed, curated, dimensional layers) of the data platform Identify the architecture, infrastructure, and interfaces to data sources, tools supporting automated data loads, security concerns, analytic models, and data visualization Perform hands-on modelling, design, schema generation and performance tuning of the data models as needed Help ensure only the right people have the right access to the right data at the right time through strategic modelling of data Work proactively and independently to address project requirements and articulate issues/challenges to reduce project delivery risks. Lead and support activities to reverse engineer data models to determine data structure of applications datasets Bring best practice modelling and keep up to date with appropriate changes in thinking with regards to methodologies Define and govern data modelling and design standards, tools, best practices, and related development for enterprise data models Create confidence in the data that is loaded onto the new schemas by monitoring and testing the data produced for integrity and quality Help determine data cleaning requirements in conjunction with the data stewards and data engineers Assist Business and Data Analysts with the development of Business Requirements Help determine data security needs in collaboration with the InfoSec and Data Governance teams QUALIFICATIONS AND REQUIREMENTS Bachelor‚Äôs or master‚Äôs degree in computer/data science or similar technical discipline. 4+ years of hands-on relational, dimensional, and analytic data modelling experience (using RDBMS, dimensional, NoSQL data platform technologies, and ETL and data ingestion protocols). Proven experience in core data modelling methodologies (e.g., Kimball, Inmon, Data Vault approaches) Experience with data warehouse, data lake, and enterprise big data platforms. Knowledge of data lake storage file formats (e.g., Parquet, JSON, CSV) Excellent knowledge and experience with SQL Good knowledge of metadata management, data modelling, and related tools required. Excellent presentation, communication and organisational skills with a high degree of agility and flexibility to meet developing business priorities Highly experienced working with databases and ETL/ELT technologies Strong attention to detail Ability to work in a fast-paced environment Knowledge of the mathematical foundations of statistical inference and forecasting will be an advantage Important: This is a fully Remote opportunity for one of our esteemed clients. Sign in Report this job Hunome (Hunomics Ltd) helps humanity make sense of itself on a collective sensemaking platform. We are a remote and diverse team of 10+. We launched the web-based platform in Q2 2021. All in the team are working shareholders. Our collective sensemaking platform helps humans build multidimensional shared understanding and we analyze and find patterns in that for our members and clients. You would represent what many would call a great commercially minded data scientist, you know what it means to be senior in that role. You are someone who is definitely wanting to make their mark in a startup, you care about what we are aiming to change in the world and you have the mindset to be consistent and persevere. Otherwise it would be just another job. An immediately salaried 'job' is not what you are after but showcasing your experience in data science within a startup with unique data for the potential for massive return with success (shares first, later salary added once funded, we progress). We make it possible for you to take the first startup step in a part-time role as a working shareholder. We‚Äôre now looking for a hands-on Data Scientist who can use their skills to evolve our data strategy, innovate new product dimensions, and propose new means to discover insights from our data. We will be guided by your analysis of company data to make smarter decisions to deliver better products. Your interest in the data engineering side would see you roadmap our AI technology evolution and the preparation of the environment. You will work closely with the product team and the technology team to excel in this role. Responsibilities (How you are expected to apply your data science skills): Define features on a roadmap Evolve our data strategy and roadmap Enhance our data collection and generation Deliver proof of concepts and then productized AI solutions along the roadmap Develop custom data models and algorithms to apply to our vertical AI/domain specific (collective sensemaking) space Define and deliver our knowledge graph and process textual data Perform time series analysis and forecasting Perform statistical analysis and reports Create the technology environment to deliver the solutions Participate in product development Role You will be joining us at a pivotal point in our development and you can expect your role to grow to: Mine and analyze data from company databases to drive optimization and improvement of product development, marketing techniques and business strategies Create automated anomaly detection systems and constant tracking of its performance Use predictive modeling to increase and optimize customer experiences, identify use cases emerging and other business outcomes Develop processes and tools to monitor and analyze model performance and data accuracy Extend the company‚Äôs data with third party sources of information when relevant Requirements (What We Expect You To Have) We‚Äôre looking for someone with 5-7 years of experience, with business applications as part of it, optimally with a Master‚Äôs degree in statistics, mathematics or computer science as a quantitative field. You would have an affinity with qualitative data and be familiar with the following: Strong problem solving skills, with innovative and analytical mind Experience with Python, and related libraries (pandas, numpy, scipy, pyplot, seaborn) Experience with Python NLP libraries (NLTK, Spacy, Gensim, Word2Vec, Glove) Knowledge of deep learning frameworks (Tensorflow, Keras) Experience with databases (SQL, PostgreSQL) Experience with data architectures Understanding of knowledge graphs and their implementation Knowledge of statistics and probability modeling Knowledge of a variety of machine learning techniques (clustering, decision tree learning, artificial neural networks, etc.) and their real-world advantages/drawbacks Experience in data visualization Familiarity with MLOps methodology and tools Nice To Have Also Azure knowledge Distributed data/computing tools: Map/Reduce, Hadoop, Hive, Kafka, Spark, Gurobi, MySQL, Neo4j etc. Other Curiosity about the potential of data Ability to work in a remote team Self-starter and innovative mind Hands-on with ambition to grow Agile and scrum are familiar Ability to train those not savvy in data analysis on its potential Ready to build something new in a startup with a mindset of discipline, team work and achievements Excellent written and verbal communication skills for coordinating across teams A drive to learn and master new technologies and techniques An ambition to make a difference in the world to how data analysis might help humanity make sense of itself Working Conditions 20hrs per week on average, arranged flexibly Remote team - Company is based in Helsinki, Finland. Diverse team in many countries English is our working language At the moment, we cannot be a sponsor of a work permit. If you wish to work in Finland, applicants should hold a work permit valid until (at least) early 2025. Please Note The team benefits by being involved on a direct equity, ownership in the company, basis for a minimum of 20hrs per week commitment for sufficient focus to become successful in the role. Once Hunome is ready to pay the salary, you would become 100% focused on the business. This means that you can build your startup career while earning a living in a day job or other part-time work. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. Sign in Report this job Minimum qualifications: Bachelor's degree in Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Industrial Engineering, or equivalent practical experience. Experience as a Facilities Manager or Chief Engineer within a critical facility. Experience managing a mission critical facilities portfolio. Preferred qualifications: Master's degree in Engineering or a related field. Experience collaborating with other business units to meet company goals and standards. Understanding of the operations and maintenance of electrical systems in a data center environment. Excellent people management and leadership skills, with the ability to influence at all levels. About The Job The Data Center team designs and operates some of the most sophisticated electrical engineering, mechanical engineering and HVAC systems in the world. Facility Technicians at Google data centers operate, monitor and support physical facilities conditions. Some duties will include heating and cooling of air and water, power supply, generators, UPS systems, electrical distribution and control and monitoring systems. You regularly help inspect, maintain and repair various data center systems such as piping and non-critical electrical or mechanical system components). You'll provide daily assistance to senior technicians as you read blueprints/schematics, conduct tours of systems and assess their working order. You will develop creative approaches to reducing operational costs while improving overall data center efficiency. You ensure that environmental and safety standards are consistently met, identifying problems and making repairs quickly In emergency situations or abnormal conditions, you manage data center performance issues and outages to minimize the recovery time from failures. In this role, you will lead a team responsible to maintain, and operate sophisticated electrical, mechanical and HVAC systems in a critical facilities environment. You will provide daily assistance across technical teams, conduct tours of systems and assess their working order. You will develop creative approaches to reducing operational costs while improving overall data center efficiency and ensuring that Environmental, Health, and Safety (EHS) standards are consistently met. You will manage data center performance issues and outages to minimize recovery time from failures. You will be responsible for generating ideas, delivering recommendations to C-level executives and driving implementation. Behind everything our users see online is the architecture built by the Technical Infrastructure team to keep it running. From developing and maintaining our data centers to building the next generation of Google platforms, we make Google's product portfolio possible. We're proud to be our engineers' engineers and love voiding warranties by taking things apart so we can rebuild them. We keep our networks up and running, ensuring our users have the best and fastest experience possible. Responsibilities Set and communicate individual and team priorities that support organizational goals. Meet regularly to discuss performance and development, and provide feedback and coaching. Ensure team members are following work processes and complying with guidelines and all sites are following facility, maintenance, and standard programs, while making recommendations for data center improvements. Monitor data center systems operation, control site activities to minimize risk, and respond effectively to any excursions or emergency procedures. Develop strategies to improve efficiency, minimize cost, and reduce environmental impact, validate and improve processes and procedures for equipment operations, and perform and analyze compliance checks for data centers globally. Collaborate with partner teams and project leads to set and implement short and long-term strategies. Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing our Accommodations for Applicants form . Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from TransPerfect Aprille Grace V. Aprille Grace V. Recruiter at TransPerfect Welcome and thank you for your interest! We are currently looking for people to participate in our Saturn project. What is the project about? The purpose of this project is to collect corporate emails which you received from businesses or organizations to help improve anti-spam and email filtering technology. A corporate email usually includes the business name or brand of a company or business, e.g. example@transperfect.com , example@yatra.com , etc. The emails should not be older than the 1st of January 2021 and should be only in English . Task description: You will share the emails in .eml or .msg formats from your personal computer (desktop or laptop), using our DataForce proprietary platform. You may submit a total of 50 emails. There are 2 types of emails needed for this project, time-sensitive emails and transactional emails. Time-sensitive emails are emails sent to an individual recipient where delivery at a specific point in time directly influences the value of the message. These are usually emails that users prefer to see in their inbox so they can act within a certain time window. For example, a meeting invitation from a company, a power outage in your house on a specific day sent by your network provider or a sudden change in flight terminal on a coming trip sent by the airline. Transactional emails are emails sent to one individual at a time. They specify recent transactions, financial statements, shipment deliveries, receipts of purchases and travel bookings. Regardless of the email category, each email must have the following attributes: - Subject line should consist of a minimum of 4 words - Sender email address should have a corporate domain name. Emails from @gmail, @yahoo, @aol, @outlook, @icloud, and other similar domains will not be accepted - Sender Name - Header (Subject, From, To and Date) Who is eligible? To participate you should meet the following qualifying criteria: - Be 18 years or older. - Be a resident of Finland. Where is the project taking place? This is a fully remote project. How much is the compensation? You will receive $1 USD for each accepted transactional email and $2.5 USD per each accepted time-sensitive email. As payment method, we offer the following options according to your country of Residence: - For residents of Finland we offer PayPal and Gift Card. Please note that all submissions will be checked by our Quality Assurance team and compensation will be provided for accepted assets. How long does it take? The task duration varies depending on how many emails you deliver and the speed of your internet connection. Sign in Report this job Direct message the job poster from F-Secure Corporation Milla Saari Milla Saari Growth | DEI | all things career F-Secure makes every digital moment more secure, for everyone. For over 35 years, we‚Äôve led the cyber security industry, protecting tens of millions of people online together with our 200+ service provider partners. We value our Fellows' individuality, with an inclusive environment where diversity drives innovation and growth. What makes you unique is what we value ‚Äì be yourself, that is (y)our greatest asset. Founded in Finland, F‚ÄëSecure has offices in Europe, North America and Asia Pacific. ---------- At F-Secure, our vision is to be #1 security experience company in the world. Recently we have created a new team, called Protection Concept Lab , to be the spearhead of innovation. We‚Äôve handpicked highly driven, motivated fellows to build this team with a mission to run a lot of experiments. These fellows have already launched multiple world‚Äôs first innovative features, protecting consumers against real scams. Fellows in this lab team are very diverse in their skillset, such as iOS developers, Android developers, Backend developers, Researchers, AI & Data Scientists. This gives this team a unique opportunity to innovate, to run experiments at a much faster pace. We seek curious and creative individual, AI & Data Scientist , with a passion for understanding how things work, including emerging scams, our product's response, and technological developments. You'll curate new ideas, initiate experiments, and collaborate with the team, product engineering, and universities. Joining at the early stage of our team's development offers a unique opportunity to shape its direction as we continuously improve our processes. As AI professionals, you'll drive innovation in AI/ML-based security features, playing a pivotal role in idea generation, experimentation, and solution conceptualization. Your responsibilities span AI model development, data analysis, software development, cloud deployment, and operations. We value diverse skill sets, so lack of expertise in certain areas or the security domain is not a concern‚Äîwe prioritize potential and adaptability. Your expertise in handling diverse data types will uncover crucial insights, initially focusing on text-related experiments but with flexibility for future exploration. Upholding ethical considerations is essential as you navigate complex terrain, ensuring privacy, transparency, and trustworthiness in AI development. Key Responsibilities Innovative Research and Development: Drive innovation in protection features across our product portfolio. Generate new ideas to address security challenges faced by consumers and partners. Validate concepts through experiments with real end-users, iterating based on feedback to enhance effectiveness and usability. Research and development against Scams : Research and develop state-of-the-art AI solution against scams using NLP. This role requires a researcher who can dive deep into the world of scams and devise innovative AI solutions to combat them. Research and develop AI Infrastructure : Manage the AI infrastructure, including deployment and optimisation of AI models. Help Data Scientists understand infrastructure potential and limitations. What are we looking for? Passion to combat scams using state-of-the-art NLP and multimodal models. Experience with NLP is a must, and multimodal experience is a big plus. Familiarity with AWS, especially SageMaker, and best MLOps practices, including model and cost optimization, auto-scaling Experience with CI/CD in high-volume, time-critical ML systems. MLOps experience in AWS. Proficiency with software development tools and processes in a fast-paced environment. Strong experience with Python. Excellent communication and leadership skills. Ability to create high-level roadmaps and communicate them to stakeholders. Knowledge of security concepts and experience with security-related projects. Bonus Points Familiarity with large models (such as LLMs). Research background in computer science or a related field. DataOps related experience. What will you get from us? You will work together with experienced and enthusiastic colleagues, and within F-Secure you will find some of the best minds in the cyber security industry. We actively encourage our Fellows to grow and develop within F-Secure, and in your career here you can find yourself contributing to any number of our other products and teams. You decide what to make of this role, what your priorities are, and how you organize your work for the best benefit to us all. We offer interesting challenges and a competitive compensation model with wide range of benefits. You get a chance to develop yourself professionally in an international and highly motivated team serving our customers in providing world class security, privacy and uncensored access to information online. You get to work in a flexible, agile, and dynamic working environment that supports individual needs. Giving our people both support and the opportunity to be in charge of their own work is something that is in our DNA. We are in a unique phase in our 30-year history and with curiosity and excitement in the air we see no limits for building a strong and fruitful career with us! Our benefits include extensive health care, remote working, company supported sport activities, lunch vouchers, regular massages and sauna at the premises and many more things to keep our best asset ‚Äì people - happy! A security vetting will possibly be conducted for the selected candidate in accordance to our employment process. The hiring team's summer holidays in July will have an affect on our availabilities. If you want to ask about the role & team, you can reach out to us by email (abdullah.al.mazed[at]f-secure.com) or on Teams on Tuesday 16th July or Wednesday 17th July between 14:30-15:00 (UTC +3, Oulu). You can book a call here: Book time with Mazed (F-Secure).
